      • isReliable

        public boolean isReliable(java.lang.String pattern)
        A pattern is reliable if it's reliability score is more than a threshold gamma. The reliability score is determined by formula (1), (2), (3) and (4) in the paper.
        Parameters:
        pattern - The pattern to be evaluated
        Returns:
        true if reliability score for patterns is higher than threshold gamma, else false.

      • nq

        private int nq(java.lang.String pi,
     java.lang.String cpj)
        NQ(x) means the number of questions satisfying a condition x. The condition pi -> cpj denotes that cpj can be extracted from a question by applying pattern pi. If cpj = '*', then the number returned is any question containing pattern pi.
        Parameters:
        pi - A reliable pattern that can generate cpj
        cpj - A set of reliable comparator pairs
        Returns:
        The number of questions that pi can extract cpj from

      • support

        private int support(java.lang.String pk_roof,
          java.lang.String cpi_roof)
        Support is defined as the support S for comparator pair cpi_roof which can be extracted by P_roof^k and does not exist in the current reliable set.
        Parameters:
        pk_roof - A candidate pattern which can extract cpi_roof
        cpi_roof - The comparator pair which can be extracted by pk_roof and does not exist in reliablePairRepository
        Returns:
        The support count for pattern p given the definition above

      • rk

        private double rk(java.lang.String pi)
        Returns a reliability score for a candidate pattern pi at iteration k. Pi can extract known reliable comparator pairs cpj. This can suffer from incomplete knowledge about reliable comparator pairs. For example, very few reliable pairs are generally discovered in early stage of bootstrapping. In this case, the score might be underestimated which could affect the effectives of distinguishing IEPs from nonreliable patterns. This problem is migitated by a lookahead procedure.
        Parameters:
        pi - The pattern for which the reliability score will be generated
        Returns:
        The reliability score for pattern pi
        See Also:
        #lookAhead()

        Returns:
